						<summary>

						<p>The record belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Koṭṭigadēva</hi> and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 893 (expired) Prajāpati (= A.D. 971).</hi> It registers a gift of <hi rend="italic">gōsahasra</hi> made by Śānta-Gāvuṇḍa to the temple constructed by him on the <hi rend="bold">11th day of the bright half of Paushya.</hi> The corresponding English date would be <hi rend="bold">A.D. 971, December 30, Saturday.</hi> Since the week-day is lost, this is not verifiable.</p>						

						<p>The inscription was composed by <hi rend="bold">Chandramauḷi-Bhaḷāra.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
